WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.330 --> 00:00:01.770
- Hi, I'm Clara.

2
00:00:01.770 --> 00:00:05.340
I work in product marketing
on the Gemini app at Google.

3
00:00:05.340 --> 00:00:08.220
Now, when I'm having
high-stakes conversations,

4
00:00:08.220 --> 00:00:11.910
like sales pitches, presentations,
or difficult one-on-ones,

5
00:00:11.910 --> 00:00:14.460
it's crucial that I'm
able to perform my best,

6
00:00:14.460 --> 00:00:16.470
really deliver the points
that I need to make

7
00:00:16.470 --> 00:00:18.030
and be persuasive.

8
00:00:18.030 --> 00:00:20.400
In this video, we're gonna use Gemini Live

9
00:00:20.400 --> 00:00:22.470
to simulate a challenging conversation

10
00:00:22.470 --> 00:00:24.750
and get feedback on how we did.

11
00:00:24.750 --> 00:00:26.490
Now, to access Gemini Live,

12
00:00:26.490 --> 00:00:29.670
you'll need to download the
Gemini mobile app on your phone.

13
00:00:29.670 --> 00:00:31.830
When we use Gemini Live,
we're not prompting,

14
00:00:31.830 --> 00:00:35.010
we're having a natural,
free-flowing conversation.

15
00:00:35.010 --> 00:00:36.930
Let's say I wanted to
practice a sales pitch

16
00:00:36.930 --> 00:00:38.670
with a potential customer.

17
00:00:38.670 --> 00:00:40.290
I'll show you what that looks like.

18
00:00:40.290 --> 00:00:42.663
To start, click into Live.

19
00:00:44.550 --> 00:00:48.150
Hey, Gemini, I need to make
an important sales call.

20
00:00:48.150 --> 00:00:49.053
Let's role-play.

21
00:00:50.610 --> 00:00:51.810
- That's a great idea.

22
00:00:51.810 --> 00:00:53.640
What kind of product are you selling?

23
00:00:53.640 --> 00:00:56.070
- So I'm a salesperson
for a logistics company

24
00:00:56.070 --> 00:00:58.230
called Cardboard Caravan.

25
00:00:58.230 --> 00:00:59.400
My goal is to book a meeting

26
00:00:59.400 --> 00:01:02.070
with the logistics manager
at Terry's Trousers,

27
00:01:02.070 --> 00:01:04.890
who recently submitted an
inquiry on our website.

28
00:01:04.890 --> 00:01:07.140
I call and you answer the phone.

29
00:01:07.140 --> 00:01:07.973
- Got it.

30
00:01:07.973 --> 00:01:10.590
I'm ready to play the logistics
manager at Terry's Trousers.

31
00:01:10.590 --> 00:01:12.090
Let's do this.

32
00:01:12.090 --> 00:01:13.860
Thank you for calling Terry's Trousers.

33
00:01:13.860 --> 00:01:15.630
How may I direct your call?

34
00:01:15.630 --> 00:01:17.910
- Hi, this is Clara
from Cardboard Caravan.

35
00:01:17.910 --> 00:01:19.530
I'm calling to follow up on an inquiry

36
00:01:19.530 --> 00:01:21.090
you submitted on our website.

37
00:01:21.090 --> 00:01:22.620
Could you tell me a little bit

38
00:01:22.620 --> 00:01:24.090
about what you're hoping to achieve

39
00:01:24.090 --> 00:01:26.040
with a new logistics partner?

40
00:01:26.040 --> 00:01:27.300
- Absolutely, Clara.

41
00:01:27.300 --> 00:01:28.830
We're looking for a logistics partner

42
00:01:28.830 --> 00:01:30.810
who can help us streamline
our shipping process

43
00:01:30.810 --> 00:01:31.800
and reduce costs.

44
00:01:31.800 --> 00:01:33.390
We've been experiencing some delays

45
00:01:33.390 --> 00:01:34.740
and inefficiencies lately,

46
00:01:34.740 --> 00:01:36.180
and we need a reliable solution

47
00:01:36.180 --> 00:01:39.330
to ensure our trousers get
to our customers on time.

48
00:01:39.330 --> 00:01:41.010
- I totally understand.

49
00:01:41.010 --> 00:01:43.110
We've helped other
companies in your position.

50
00:01:43.110 --> 00:01:44.790
Would you be open to a
brief follow-up meeting

51
00:01:44.790 --> 00:01:47.460
to talk about how we could
help you specifically?

52
00:01:47.460 --> 00:01:49.110
- I'm sure that could be arranged.

53
00:01:49.110 --> 00:01:51.570
What times are you
available for a meeting?

54
00:01:51.570 --> 00:01:52.530
- How about next week?

55
00:01:52.530 --> 00:01:55.920
I can follow up via email
and send you a case study?

56
00:01:55.920 --> 00:01:57.600
- Sure. Next week works.

57
00:01:57.600 --> 00:01:59.430
Please send the case study.

58
00:01:59.430 --> 00:02:01.440
- Now that we finished
our Live conversation,

59
00:02:01.440 --> 00:02:03.510
we can ask Gemini for feedback.

60
00:02:03.510 --> 00:02:07.590
We'll ask Gemini to provide
feedback on my approach,

61
00:02:07.590 --> 00:02:10.050
includes strengths, weaknesses,

62
00:02:10.050 --> 00:02:11.883
and suggestions for improvement.

63
00:02:14.010 --> 00:02:14.843
Huh.

64
00:02:17.070 --> 00:02:17.970
Wow.

65
00:02:17.970 --> 00:02:19.290
There's some great feedback in here

66
00:02:19.290 --> 00:02:21.243
that I can definitely use to practice.

67
00:02:22.950 --> 00:02:25.530
I also use this feature
to talk through ideas,

68
00:02:25.530 --> 00:02:28.740
and then turn those into
actionable project proposals.

69
00:02:28.740 --> 00:02:30.690
Say I have an out-of-the-box concept

70
00:02:30.690 --> 00:02:32.280
for a new product launch.

71
00:02:32.280 --> 00:02:34.770
I'll ask Gemini Live to help
me flesh out the concept,

72
00:02:34.770 --> 00:02:38.430
and then synthesize our
conversation into an action plan

73
00:02:38.430 --> 00:02:40.200
that I can share with my leadership

74
00:02:40.200 --> 00:02:42.090
and with clearly-outlined next steps.

75
00:02:42.090 --> 00:02:45.483
It's a great way to go
from idea to execution.

76
00:02:46.320 --> 00:02:48.570
So the next time you
want another perspective

77
00:02:48.570 --> 00:02:49.890
or help with ideation,

78
00:02:49.890 --> 00:02:51.453
try going Live with Gemini.